<TITLE> Police recover youth's body </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, May 1 (bdnews24.com) The police recovered a body at Ullahpara in Sirajganj on Saturday. The dead youth was identified as Selim, son of Abdul Hannan of Khaduli village of Bara Pangasi union of Ullahpara upazila. Md Abbas Ali, a sub-inspector of Ullahpara Police Station said that Selim had goon missing since Friday night. Ali said that criminals had slaughtered Selim with sharp weapons. Wounds were visible in different pars of the body, Ali said. He said that police recovered the body from a swamp of Khaduli village after they had been informed by the locals. The police will primarily investigate whether a radical leftist groups were involved. A case was filed in this connection. bd
